{
  "stem": "1733.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 192.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, the-- there were two other boys, from our area, from Velike Loucky-- it was called Nagy Lucska during the Hungarians-- that were called in at the same time as I was.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And matter of fact, I had a cousin there, from [NON-ENGLISH], also a Katz boy.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And all-- all-- all the kids that were in that camp were 21 years old.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, they were called in at the same time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was nice friendship between us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they-- they were disciplinarians.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it wasn't anything out of ordinary that you need to pay attention.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No, they were-- they were friendly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were-- they-- they were trying to scare us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were having fun.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They piled us up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They-- they made us go on a-- on a pile of garbage and tamp down the garbage and sing Hungarian songs, that they were directed.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, they were just having a lot of fun with us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That was a couple of days before the march from Budapest, that they were taking us into Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I would like to point out, at this time, that my mother was taken away in April.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But June, I received a postcard from her in camp, while I was in Budakalasz, telling me that they are doing well, not to worry about them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Which, now I know-- which now I know that they made them before they killed them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They made them write a card, to anybody that they had left at home, which served a double purpose, to find out whether anybody was hiding and, also, to confuse anybody that received the card, to find out and, you know, to let us know that they are-- they are doing well.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The card-- excuse me.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
